

Methods - block or group of statements which will perform certain task.
          we have to call the method though object


FOUR ways to create the method
--------------------------------------
1) No parameter , No Return value
2) No parameter , Return value
3) Takes parameter , No Return value
4) Takes parameter , Return value

How many ways we can store data into variable
1) by using object reference variable
2) method
3) constructor



*Constructor-
----------------------------------------------
- Constructor name should be same as CLASS
- Their is no return value not even void
- It Takes parameter , No Return value

type of Constructor
1) Default Constructor
2) Parameterize Constructor




Difference between Method and Constructor

Method
---------------------------
1) Method name can be anything
2) Method may or may not return a value
3) If method is not returning any value then specify void
4) Method can take parameters/arguments
5) We have to invoke/call the method explicitly through object
6) Used for specific login

Constructor
---------------------------
1) Constructor name should be same as class name
2) Constructor will never return a value( not even void)
3) We don't specify the void
4) Constructor can take parameters/arguments
5) Constructor automatically invoked/called at the time of object creation
6) Used for initialise the value of the variable


















